title: Review of the Mine Action Strategy
description: Through the Mine Action Strategy for the Australian aid program, the Government committed $100 million to reduce the threat and socioeconomic impact of landmines, cluster munitions and other explosive remnants of war over the period 2010-2014. The Strategy includes a commitment to review the Strategy at its completion to measure the effectiveness, efficiency and impact of Australia's mine action and to further improve and develop Australia's mine action assistance.
